HEADWORD: Charqui
<hw>Char"qui</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp. A term used
in South America, Central America, and the Western United States.]</ety>
<def>Jerked beef; beef cut into long strips and dried in the wind and
sun.</def> <rj><au>Darwin.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

